To pick one moronic point, Amazon affiliate code is a code that bloggers etc can use to link to products on Amazon and get a small percent if the person who entered that site using the link buys something.

Duckduckgo appends one of these codes when it links to Amazon. They only have to do this at all because unlike other search engines they link in a way that doesn't leak a referrer address (you could configure your browser to do this by default). In other search engines Amazon knows that you came from that search engine results page, and exactly what you typed into that search engine.

With the affiliate code Amazon only knows that you followed a link with that affiliate code in it or you typed the link in manually, they can't tell the difference.
